<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ920212-0056</DOCNO><DOCID>920212-0056.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Applied Materials Inc.:   Net Income Increased 51%   In Firm's Fiscal 1st Period</HL><DATE>02/12/92</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C13</SO><CO>   AMAT</CO><MS>TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>EARNINGS (ERN)SEMICONDUCTORS, INTEGRATED CHIPS (SEM)</IN><NS>EARNINGS (ERN)</NS><RE>CALIFORNIA (CA)NORTH AMERICA (NME)PACIFIC RIM (PRM)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   Applied Materials Inc. said fiscal first-quarter netsurged 51% to $6.4 million, or 37 cents a share, amid strongsales and orders for its semiconductor manufacturingequipment.   The Santa Clara, Calif., company earned $4.2 million, or25 cents a share, a year earlier. Sales in the period, endedJan. 31, were $167 million, up 16% from $144.6 million.</LP><TEXT>   New orders hit a record $219 million during the quarter,and the company's backlog rose to $265 million, largelybecause of demand for machines that make eight-inch wafers ofadvanced design. Gross margins declined slightly, in partbecause of recent changes in the company's product mix. Butthat decline was offset by lower relative operating expenses,the company said.   In national over-the-counter trading, the company's stockwas quoted at $36.75, down 75 cents a share.</TEXT></DOC>